This is the Recipients Landing overlay. Here, users will find all of their recipients under ‘Pending’ and ‘Recipients’. This page
is accessible from the Payment Landing page header ‘View all’ icon or the Payments Landing page 'Manage' tab, in the My
The primary CTA on this page is to add a new recipient. This button will always be visible to the user when on this
page. Clicking this button will start the ‘add new recipient’ flow.
Since this is the first level overlay experience, the ‘x’ icon will still be visible for users to act on. If the user clicks on
the ‘x’ icon then it would exit the overlay experience and return the user to where they accessed this screen, on the
This section houses the table controls. From here a user will be able to search, filter, print, and export the table. Print
Typing into the search bar will filter the table contextually by what the user inputs into the search bar. This search will
include Recipient Name as well as Email.
Selection of the filter icon will bring an overlay of filter options in which to filter the table by. Once the options are
selected the table will filter by the users selections.
Selection of the print icon will launch the print dialog of the user’s browser. All items on the page will be printed if no
rows are individually selected. If there are rows selected, only the items selected will be printed.
Selection of the export icon will prompt a dialog to appear. The dialog will allow the user the option to customize the
exported data and in their preferred format (CSV or XML). Following this step, the user is led to their browser’s save
dialog window to continue with the export.
On default, the Pending Recipients table will load 10 line items initially, and 5 in mobile. If the OU has more than this
number of recipients in the Pending Recipients table, the ‘View More’ text link is available at the bottom of the table.
The user can select this link to load more line items. This is not a feature in the Active Recipients table.
The dropdown icon here in the Active Recipient table is available to user on all active recipients. When selected they
are able to Suspend, Delete, Make Payment, or view recipient Payment History. All actions that are available on the
recipient details page. The quick action menu allows easier access to their respective flows without going through
When a recipient is suspended, the only differences are:
- the status from active to suspended.
- payments cannot be made to a suspended recipient. Pending payments will be sent to draft, and any payments
already sent to the recipient will not be any effected.
The dropdown icon here in the Pending Recipients table will be visible next to the line item if the user has the
authorization to approve the recipient. When selected, the dropdown will give the option to either ‘Approve’ or ‘Send
Back’ the pending recipient. This allows the user to enter the Approve or Send Back flow directly. Clicking on the line
item will open the pending Recipient Details screen, which will give user the same option as CTAs.
If the user is not an authorizer or is unable to authorize the recipient because they are the creator or editor of the
recipient, no dropdown options are available.
